== Gravitation == === Kepler's Laws === # The orbit of each planet is an ellipse which has the sun at one of its foci. # Each planet moves in such a way that the line joining it to the sun sweeps out equal areas in equal times. # The squares of the periods of revolution of the planets about the Sun are proportional to the cubes of their mean distance from it.
=== Newton's gravitational law === <math>F = G\frac{m_1 m_2}{r^2}</math> {| style="margin-left: 2em;" | style="text-align: right;" | ''F'' = | The gravitational force between two bodies. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''G'' = | Universal gravity constant, 6.67 x 10<sup>&minus;11</sup> N m<sup>2</sup> kg<sup>&minus;2</sup> |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''m<sub>1</sub>'' = | The mass of the first body. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''m<sub>2</sub>'' = | The mass of the second body. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''r'' = | The distance between the centres of mass of two bodies. |}
== Black body radiation == temperature of the black body. :''w'' = 2.90 &times; 10<sup>&minus;3</sup> m K
=== Stefan's Law === <math>E = {\sigma}{T^4}</math> {| style="margin-left: 2em;" | style="text-align: right;" | ''E'' = | Rate of energy radiated from the surface of a black body per unit area. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''&sigma;'' = | Stefan's constant, 5.67 &times; 10<sup>&minus;8</sup> W m<sup>&minus;2</sup> K<sup>&minus;4</sup> |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''T'' = | Surface temperature of the black body. |}
== Stellar Magnitude == === Apparent Magnitude === <math>m = -2.5 \log_{10} I + K</math> {| style="margin-left: 2em;" | style="text-align: right;" | ''m'' = | Apparent magnitude of star. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''I'' = | Intensity of light received. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''K'' = | a constant |}
=== Pogson's Formula === <math>m_1 - m_2 = 2.5 \log_{10} \left(\frac{I_2}{I_1}\right)</math> {| style="margin-left: 2em;" | style="text-align: right;" | ''m<sub>1</sub>'' = | Apparent magnitude of first star. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''m<sub>2</sub>'' = | Apparent magnitude of second star. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''I<sub>1</sub>'' = | Intensity of light received from first star. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''I<sub>2</sub>'' = | Intensity of light received from second star. |} === Absolute Magnitude === <math>m - M = 5 \log_{10} \left(\frac{d}{10}\right)</math> {| style="margin-left: 2em;" | style="text-align: right;" | ''m'' = | Apparent magnitude of star. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''M'' = | Absolute magnitude of star. |- | style="text-align: right;" | ''d'' = | Distance to star in parsecs. |}
