{{Ada/Navigation|Libraries|Ada.Strings.Unbounded.Text_IO}}
__TOC__

{{Ada/package|Ada|Strings|Unbounded|Text_IO}} is a GNAT implementation-defined package that offers Get_Line and Put_Line functions which work directly on unbounded strings. They are more efficient and easier to use than the standard {{Ada/package|Ada|Text_IO}} functions.

 {{Ada/kw|function}} Get_Line {{Ada/kw|return}} Unbounded_String;

 {{Ada/kw|function}} Get_Line (File : {{Ada/package|Ada|Text_IO}}.File_Type) {{Ada/kw|return}} Unbounded_String;

Reads up to the end of the current line, returning the result as an unbounded string of appropriate length. If no File parameter is present, input is from Current_Input.

 {{Ada/kw|procedure}} Put      (U    : Unbounded_String); 
 {{Ada/kw|procedure}} Put      (File : {{Ada/package|Ada|Text_IO}}.File_Type;  U : Unbounded_String); 
 {{Ada/kw|procedure}} Put_Line (U    : Unbounded_String); 
 {{Ada/kw|procedure}} Put_Line (File : {{Ada/package|Ada|Text_IO}}.File_Type;  U : Unbounded_String);

These are equivalent to the standard Text_IO routines passed the value To_String (U), but operate more efficiently, because the extra copy of the argument is avoided.

In [[Ada Programming/Ada 2005|Ada 2005]] the standard equivalent to this package is {{Ada/package|Ada|Text_IO|Unbounded_IO}}.

