== ط ‹tâ›, ظ ‹zâ› ==
{| align=right class=PrettyTextBox style="background-color: rgb(249, 249, 249); margin-bottom: 1em;" dir=rtl
|- style="font-size:200%; font-family:{{Persian/fonts-simple}}; line-height:1.5em"
| ط || ظ
|-
| ‹tâ› || ‹zâ›
|}
The next two Persian letters have the same shape, but only one has a dot.

<br style="clear:both" />
{{Persian/Connecting letters box | Arab=ط|audio=fa-ط.ogg|Latn=tâ}}
The letter {{term-fa|ط|tâ}} is another Persian letter for the sound /t/.

<br style="clear:both" />
{{Persian/Connecting letters box | Arab=طاس|Latn=tâs| ط&zwj; |s| &zwj;ا |â| س |s}}
As shown in the word {{term-fa| طاس |tâs|bald}} on the right, the letter <big> ط </big> joins with the letter that follows it.

<br style="clear:both" />
{{Persian/Connecting letters box | Arab=ظ| Latn=zâ}}
The letter {{term-fa|ظ|zâ}} is another Persian letter for the sound /z/.  It is rare and only appears in words of Arabic origin.

<big> ظ </big> joins with the letter that follows it.

