|-valign="top"
| width="50%" | Core vocabulary:
{{Persian/vocab-list|hide Arab=yes
|آقا|'''â'''qâ|/ˈɒːɣɒː/|Mr.|
|حال|'''hâl'''|/ˈhɒːl/|health|
|شما|šo'''mâ'''|/ʃoˈmɒː/|you|(formal, shows speaker's respect for listener)
|چطور|ce'''tor'''|/t͡ʃeˈtoɾ/|how|
|خدا حافظ|xo'''dâ''' hâ'''fez'''|/xoˈdɒː hɒːˈfez/|May God keep you|(similar to “goodbye”, “God be with you”)
}}
* ‹'''hâl'''-e šo'''mâ''' ce'''tor''' e?› — "How is your health?"
* ‹man '''xub''' '''hast'''am.› — “I am well.”
* ‹šo'''mâ''' ce'''tor'''in?› — “How are you?” (formal)

