{{Persian/top}}

In [[Persian/Lesson 1|lessons 1]], [[Persian/Lesson 2|2]], and [[Persian/Lesson 3|3]], you learned some greetings, the first twenty-nine letters of the Persian Alphabet, and how to spell and pronounce several words with those letters.

In this lesson, you will learn the final three letters (ﻭ ‹vâv›, ﻩ ‹he› and ى ‹ye›), diacritics, and the remaining rules for reading and writing Persian vowels.  You will also learn about a Persian tradition called ‹haft sin›.

